cs.SI, cs.CL, cs.SOC, cs.CYBER, cs.MM

This paper analyzes the lexicons used by communities of users on Facebook, which suggests a focus on social media (cs.SOC) and natural language processing (cs.CL). The study also examines the phenomenon of echo chambers, which relates to the field of social informatics (cs.SI). Additionally, the paper discusses the spread of misinformation, which could fall under the category of cybersecurity (cs.CYBER). Finally, the analysis of comment threads and the emergence of collective identities could also relate to multimedia (cs.MM) as it involves the study of user interactions with content.
